        "title": "refactor: extract media and ACP core packages",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Extract media primitives into private `@openclaw/media-core` and ACP runtime/shared types into private `@openclaw/acp-core`.\n- Rewire core, plugin SDK, package-boundary, native/Jiti SDK aliases, UI aliases, watch paths, and tsdown/package build inputs to the new internal packages.\n- Carry forward main's media response timeout clamp behavior into `media-core` and fix latest-main auth expiry type narrowing so core typecheck stays green.\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: internal package refactor for media primitives and ACP runtime/shared helpers without changing user-facing behavior.\nReal environment tested: local macOS source checkout on current `origin/main` (`b372af6b81`).\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/input-files.fetch-guard.test.ts packages/media-core/src/base64.test.ts packages/media-core/src/mime.test.ts packages/media-core/src/inbound-path-policy.test.ts packages/media-core/src/inline-image-data-url.test.ts packages/media-core/src/read-byte-stream-with-limit.test.ts packages/media-core/src/read-response-with-limit.test.ts src/plugins/sdk-alias.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-sdk-native-resolver.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/extension-package-project-boundaries.test.ts src/infra/watch-node.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm check:import-cycles`\n- `pnpm --filter @openclaw/media-core build && pnpm --filter @openclaw/acp-core build`\n- `node scripts/check-extension-package-tsc-boundary.mjs`\n- `pnpm deps:shrinkwrap:check`\n- `node scripts/build-all.mjs ciArtifacts`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --prompt 'Context: do not require adding @openclaw/media-core or @openclaw/acp-core as root package.json dependencies. Root npm shrinkwrap generation rejects workspace:* in package.json; these internal package imports follow the existing bundled/tsconfig alias pattern used by normalization/media-generation/terminal packages. Also, use node scripts/build-all.mjs ciArtifacts for the CI-time build target; full pnpm build intentionally includes slower declaration package builds.'`\nEvidence after fix: focused Vitest shards passed 6/6; extension package boundary passed for 112 plugins plus 2 canaries in 102.1s; `ciArtifacts` build passed in 49.7s; full `pnpm build` passed in 195.3s; final autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: media/ACP helpers resolve from package boundaries, plugin SDK declarations stay resolvable, import cycles remain at 0, and core typecheck is green.\nWhat was not tested: no live provider/channel or cross-OS Crabbox run; this is an internal package-boundary refactor with local package, SDK, UI, build, and boundary proof.\n",
